info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued March 16 at 3:21PM CDT until March 17 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM CDT FRIDAY... * WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Additional snow accumulations of 5 to 10 inches. Amounts of up to 12 inches are possible for the higher terrain of Cook county. Amounts will be lower near Lake Superior. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph will cause blowing and drifting snow. * WHERE...Northern Cook and Lake, Southern Lake and Southern Cook Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Grand Portage Reservation. * WHEN...Until 10 PM CDT Friday. * IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.
